  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. In right triangle ABC with the right angle at C, AB is the hypotenuse and AC is the leg adjacent to angle A. So cos(A) = AC/AB = 28/35.</p><p>Choice A is the reciprocal (1/cos A). Choice B uses an unrelated side. Choice D divides 1 by the adjacent side.</p>",
